      • isPermute

        public static boolean isPermute(int a,
                                int b)
        Determines if two positive integers are permutations of one another.

        Two positive integers are permutations if they contain the same digits in the same quantities. For instance, 1234 and 4321 are permutations. Also, 1203 and 1230 are permutations of each other, while 0123 is not. (Leading zeros are not allowed in number definitions.) Finally, n is a permutation of itself, for all integers n.
